If the end of 2021 was me reaching the top of a mountain (which is what it felt like), 2022 has either been the slow descent into the valley or the slow ascent of the next mountain...I haven't quite figured that out....didn't have much peace or calm this year, but gained a lot of love and wisdom...didn't listen to hardly any music, watched a lot of movies....slept less, worried more, ate more, cried more, cleaned less ... I know it sounds like a bust, but somehow it was great too....messy and great and hard.... because as a control freak who also loves experiencing life, that's how it is...I don't know what I accomplished, I wasn't keeping track...2023 will be another year...the world keeps spinning...we're all just looking at old light anyways

So excited that, Fancy Dance, the beautiful film that I have composed my first ever feature length score for, is premiering at @sundanceorg on Jan 20 at Eccles Theatre in Park City, UT!!! This was such an amazing honor to be asked to contribute and it has ignited a real passion for this type of work and I hope I get to engage in more work like this in the future. Life is a gift 🎁 
Yakoke to @ericajtremblay for trusting me to add layers to your important story and all the solid folks at Confluential Films and JTN Music and @communionmusic for helping guide me through my first scoring!
Thanks also to @brinewebb and @kylereidmusic for their great work and ideas as well! 
If you're gonna be at Sundance Film Fest, make sure you catch the movie!! Starring @lilygladstone @isabel47222 and even a cheeky cameo from @redcorn

Hard to believe that this record, Kid Face, came out 10 years ago today! I worked at a now shut restaurant here in Norman called Local for 11 months and saved up all of my tip money in a drawer. Then when the time came I put all of that tip money in a paper bag and drove out to San Francisco with my band to record at Tiny Telephone OG (rip) with @johnvanderslice and @jacobwinik .... Fantastic hangs with the personnel on this record... @veryfamousdrummer @johncalvinabney @kylereidmusic @danielfoulks @brinewebb @smannasmash ... Released by @ramseurrecords and @fulltimehobbyrecords 

My favorite story about the making of this record is probably the fact that the majority of Daniel's fiddle parts were recorded in an isolated echo chamber where he couldn't hear the song at all while we were recording him. We just let him hear the beginning of the song and he had to sort of by memory follow along with the song and play along what he thought would happen, but he was really just in an isolated silent chamber. This led to some very exciting sounds I think.

What's your favorite song off of Kid Face?

Samantha Crain is a Choctaw singer, songwriter, poet, producer, and musician from Oklahoma. She is a three-time Native American Music Award winner and winner of an Indigenous Music Award. Her genre spanning discography has been critically acclaimed by media outlets such as Rolling Stone, SPIN, Paste, No Depression, NPR, PRI, The Guardian, NME, Uncut, and others. She has toured extensively over the past 15 years nationally and internationally, presenting ambitious orchestrated shows with a band and intimate folk leaning solo performances. She has toured with First Aid Kit, Neutral Milk Hotel, Gregory Alan Isakov, The Avett Brothers, The Mountain Goats, Brandi Carlile, Langhorne Slim, The Staves, and many other bands and artists. With her new album, “A Small Death”, and newer EP, “I Guess We Live Here Now”, she continues her tradition of keeping things close to the heart and the ground by leaning into the fulfillment of affinity with an audience and the satisfaction of a song with a memorable melody and an honest story. Most recently, she has composed the score for the award-winning film, Fancy Dance.
